  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Excelsior is on either bed and breakfast, or half board. </p>
<p>Each morning a varied hot and cold breakfast buffet is served. In the evenings you can enjoy a four course meal inspired by Swiss and French cuisine. </p>
<p>The Hotel Excelsior has two on-site a la carte restaurants, the Restaurant La Ferme which specialises in traditional dishes and grilled meats, their house speciality is the  “Flambée Medici” – a tender beef fillet prepared for you at the table. There is also the <span>Luna restaurant serving traditional cheese fondue.</span></p>
<p><span>The Ex-Bar is a great place to enjoy a drink or two, whether its after skiing or after dinner, there will be a drink to suit you.</span></p>
<p> </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>Considered a hidden gem in <a data-udi="umb://document/4abc3d9367fc4903a52b296414b05ef1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4abc3d9367fc4903a52b296414b05ef1}" title="Zermatt">Zermatt</a>, the Hotel Excelsior is a cosy family-run hotel which prides itself on personal service and great views of the Matterhorn.</p>
<h2>Matterhorn Views</h2>
<p>The Hotel Excelsior is in a prime location just <span>250 metres to Zermatt's centre with plenty of shops and restaurants, and </span><span>400 metres to the Gornergratbahn and the Sunnegga Express funicular.  </span><span>The hotel has incredible views of the Swiss Alps, many of the rooms have either village views or look out onto the iconic Matterhorn. We recommend opting for a Double South Matterhorn View room where you can watch the sunrise over the spectacular mountains.</span></p>
<h2>Food &amp; Wine </h2>
<p>Available<span> on Half Board or Bed &amp; Breakfast, the Hotel Excelsior has options for everyone. The restaurant uses seasonal and local produce where possible,  fuel up for the day at the extensive breakfast buffet with a variety of hot and cold options, when you return in the evening sample the four course menu inspired by the French and Swiss cuisines. Be sure to try out the restaurant's popular wine list with many bottles coming from the nearby Canton Valais vineyard region.</span></p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
